ji, A.T., Shoremekun, K.L. and Yakubu, M.T. 2009. Physicochemical properties of the oil from the fruit of <i>Blighia sapida </i>and toxicological evaluation of the oil-based diet in Wistar rats. <i>Journal of Medicinal Food</i><i>&nbsp;</i>12 (1): 127–1,135.</p><p>Royes, H.H. and Baccus, G.R. 1988. Orchard crops. The Jamaica Farmer’s Guide, Jamaica Agricultural Society, Kingston, Jamaica. p. 108.</p><p>Scott, H. 1916. On vomiting sickness of Jamaica. Annual Medical Parasitology 10: 1–8.</p><p>Seaforth, C.E. 1963. The ackee: Jamaica’s national fruit<i>. </i>Bulletin of the Scientific Research Council 3: 51–53.</p><p>Shakespeare-Blackmore, K. 2007. Ackee flies high again. The Gleaner,<i>&nbsp;</i>11 January.</p><p>Statistical Institute of Jamaica, 2002. External Trade. Statistical Institute of Jamaica 2:<b>&nbsp;</b>56–57.</p><p>Tanaka K., Kean E. A. and Johnson B. 1976. Jamaican vomiting sickness. Biochemical investigations of two cases. New England Journal of Medicine<i>&nbsp;</i>295: 461-467.</p>
